added.title: Tower Power
added.description: Cyborg plugs into the control panel of the Titans' tower and drives the others crazy.

added.title: Parasite
added.description: Starfire's new pet is a horribly dangerous parasite, but Robin is the only one who is suspicious of the beast.

added.title: Starliar
added.description: Beast Boy teaches Starfire how to lie and it backfires as her lies get more and more outrageous.

added.title: Staff Meeting
added.description: When the gang breaks Robin's beloved staff, Robin is forced to find a replacement.

added.title: Meatball Party
added.description: Raven eats a bad meatball that causes tentacles to spring from her teeth and devour the other Titans.

added.title: The Picnic
added.description: Gumball and Darwin barely survive a school picnic in the Forest of Doom

added.title: The Goons
added.description: Gumball sets out to win his Dad back by winning a blindfolded "dumb" race.

added.title: The Secret
added.description: Gumball almost loses his mind trying to guess Darwin's secret.

added.title: The Sock
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are taught confusing lessons about honesty by the school councillor.

added.title: The Genius
added.description: Darwin is sent away to a government institute for geniuses. Yes. Really.

added.title: The Future is Cardboard
added.description: The kids meet an eccentric Cardboard Creator that invites Craig to help finish his masterpiece.

added.title: The Brood
added.description: Craig's determination to get his granddad a cicada shell causes him, Kelsey and JP to become trapped in their stump!

added.title: Under the Overpass
added.description: Craig and his friends travel to find honeysuckle in the creek but discover a whole new part of the creek.

added.title: Heatwave
added.description: Apple and Onion try to spread cheer during a city-wide heatwave.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: After learning that Burger has a trampoline, Apple and Onion pay him a visit. Burger thinks they came especially to see him and is overjoyed.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple and Onion run out of toilet paper because Apple's been building a huge modern art sculpture with it. They're going to need more if Apple is to finish and Onion is to be able to resume his normal toilet activities.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple is in danger of losing his best friend.

added.title: Dog Hotel
added.description: With no place to stay while their cave gets fumigated, the Bears book a night at a hotel for dogs.

added.title: Bear Lift
added.description: To help raise money to save Darrell's store, the Bears use the stack as a taxi through a ride share app.

added.title: The Nom Nom Show
added.description: Things go awry while Nom Nom shoots his first television show. The Bears offer to help and appear on the show.

added.title: Ice Cave
added.description: Ralph takes over the cave and turns it into a snowy fortress where he reigns as king over the Bears and Charlie.

added.title: Spa Day
added.description: The Bears have a relaxing day at the spa. Grizz tries to get everything the spa has to offer. Panda gets trapped in the steam room with an old man. And Ice Bear plays ping pong.

added.title: Nightmare Hospital
added.description: Steven and Connie sneak into a hospital to recover Rose's Sword.

added.title: Sadie's Song
added.description: Steven helps Sadie put together an act for Beachapalooza.

added.title: Catch and Release
added.description: We finally see inside Steven's bathroom.

added.title: When It Rains
added.description: Steven helps a friend who's afraid of thunderstorms.

added.title: Back to the Barn
added.description: Steven and the Gems head back to the family barn to build some robots.

added.title: Freak City
added.description: A magical man turns Finn into a foot. They meet others who have been similarly wronged and must work together.

added.title: Ocean of Fear
added.description: Finn faces his biggest challenge yet, overcoming his fear of water.

added.title: When Wedding Bells Thaw
added.description: Finn must help plan the Ice King's bachelor party.

added.title: The Duke
added.description: Finn goes to great lengths to catch the evil Duke of Nuts, only to discover he's not such a bad guy after all.

added.title: Donny
added.description: In an attempt to save a village, Finn and Jake rehabilitate Donny the Ogre, who's a real jerk.

added.title: Caveman
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to civilize a caveman so that Benson will let him stay at the park.

added.title: That's My Television
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to help their favorite 80's sitcom star escape to the mountains.

added.title: A Bunch of Full Grown Geese
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get rid of some geese that are causing problems at the park.

added.title: Fool Me Twice
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to win the grand prize on a Japanese game show.

added.title: Limousine Lunchtime
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to clean Maellard's limo before he gets back from vacation.

added.title: Monkey Love
added.description: When Blossom makes a bad call, she becomes afraid to try again.

added.title: Bridezilla
added.description: When Mojo and Barbarus announce their wedding, the girls are convinced that they're up to no good.

added.title: Find Your Bliss
added.description: When Bubbles blames a string of accidents on her imaginary friend Bliss, her sisters begin to think she's lost her mind.

added.title: Bliss Reminisce
added.description: The Girls learn Bliss' backstory from the Professor, Mojo Jojo, and Bliss herself.

added.title: Blisster Sister
added.description: The Girls hang out with their new big sister Bliss, who gets a taste of fighting bad guys as part of the Powerpuff Girls.

added.title: Beep
added.description: To help combat bummer feelings, Unikitty's installed Bad Vibe detectors throughout the castle. But soon, annoying beeping detectors fill the halls, and they can't find the source of the bad vibes or shut off the sound! It would seem someone's not owning up to being in a bad mood.Will the friends figure out who is secretly a Negative Nancy, or will they lose their mind to beeping madness?

added.title: Delivery Effect
added.description: Unikitty and gang have ordered some delicious Thai food for dinner.  Unfortunately the wait for the delivery is proving too much, time itself seems to have slowed down. In an effort to get the food their faster the gang utilizes Dr. Fox's time machine, which causes big problems and really hurts Father Time's feelings.

added.title: Lazer Tag
added.description: When the Score creeper traps Unikitty and the gang in his laser tag arena the gang must defeat the house team or be imprisoned forever.

added.title: Trapped in Paradise
added.description: Unikitty and the gang have crashed on a fabulous island. It's really nice and no one wants to leave until Richard convinces them that they need to return to the Kingdom and deal with their responsibilities. Unfortunately every attempt to escape the island is sabotaged. Now they must find the culprit to ensure their return home.

added.title: Safety First
added.description: Concerned about Puppycorn's propensity to hurt himself constantly, the gang places him into Richard's old Safety Suit. The suit does indeed keep him safe, but when Puppycorn purposefully puts himself in danger the suit goes into lock down, and won't allow him to move. Now the gang must figure out a way to get him out of the Safety Suit.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: Clarence struggles to make a connection at an all-girls slumber party, leaving Sumo and Jeff at odds without Clarence as their "friendship buffer."

added.title: Nature Clarence
added.description: Clarence, Sumo and Jeff's nature hike veers off course courtesy of their under qualified, overwhelmed guide Josh, prompting Clarence to take the lead.

added.title: Average Jeff
added.description: Jeff suffers an identity crisis when a standardized test lands him in the lesser of the classes academic groupings.

added.title: Lizard Day Afternoon
added.description: Clarence and Sumo chase a lizard to unexpected rewards as Jeff jockeys for playing time on Belson's spectacular new gaming system.

added.title: The Forgotten
added.description: After Clarence and his indecisive classmate Brady are left behind at school, Brady is forced to tag along on Clarence's adventure home.

added.title: Bottom Bag
added.description: After receiving a new bag friend, Belly Bag has to realize its nefarious intentions to completely replace Belly Bag and stop it before it's too late.

added.title: Watermelon Gag
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets a watermelon stuck in his mouth, he is unable to ask for help and people interpret it as a comedy routine. As Uncle Grandpa's popularity rises, his friendships and morale suffer.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Babies
added.description: When the President calls in the Uncle Grandpa babies, they have to act quickly and use their special baby powers to defuse a missile.

added.title: Birdman
added.description: When Birdman makes the RV's attic his new home, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must figure out a way to make him leave before they're all driven crazy.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Retires
added.description: Uncle Grandpa discovers a new, unusual occupation.
